  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Camp Coordination and Camp Management and Emergency Shelter and Non-Food items (NFI) assistance for conflict affected populations in Northern Ethiopia.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this $3.5 million IOM project is to provide Camp Coordination and Camp Management and Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items (NFI) assistance for conflict-affected populations in Northern Ethiopia. Among other activities, IOM and its implementing partners will provide the full package of Camp Coordination and Camp Management and Emergency activities which will include site improvement and infrastructure works, coordination and monitoring of services, establishing and providing refresher sessions for IDPs self-governance structures, including on Participation and Inclusion; as well as Community Feedback Mechanisms (CFMs). IOM CCCM will develop a Protection refresher module for IDP Community Representatives on the issue of Participation &amp; Inclusion. IOM will also provide life-saving emergency shelter, NFI (in-kind), and cash for rent support in the Amhara, Afar, and Tigray regions of Ethiopia. The project provides life-saving assistance to 269,625 people, including 57,859 women, 54,554  men, 80,203 girls,77,009  boys, and 23,295 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
